  "text": "My friend is #opentowork!\n\n🛠️ #DevOps, #Python, #PowerShell, #Linux, #AWS, #Azure, #technicalwriting\n\n😎 I've personally met Vuyisile Ndlovu as a speaker at PyCon Namibia 2020 (Windhoek) and the Ubuntu Summit 2022 (Prague). We've traveled together, had fun together. I can totally recommend him as a great addition to your team.\n\n🦸‍♂️ He's the author of \"PyPI in a box\", a portable PyPI server based on Raspberry Pi. Since 2011 he writes a blog, where he shares tips about what he's learned, and which I like to read on regular basis. He has been invited to multiple podcasts, including Profitable Python, PyDev Of The Week, Built in Africa, Python Bytes, CodeBytes, The Mycelium Network.",
